<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2013/07/10/spring-tool-suite-and-groovy-grails-tool-suite-3-3-0-released">Spring Tool Suite and Groovy/Grails Tool Suite 3.3.0 released</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/8491f7d4276bddcfdcefaf5ae860b9f6?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/mlippert">Martin Lippert</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2013-07-10 11:24:00.0">July 10, 2013</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="1124" href="/blog/2013/07/10/spring-tool-suite-and-groovy-grails-tool-suite-3-3-0-released#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Dear Spring Community,</p>
<p>we are happy to announce the next major release of our Eclipse-based tooling today: The Spring Tool Suite (STS) 3.3.0 and the Groovy/Grails Tool Suite (GGTS) 3.3.0.</p>
<p>Highlights from this release include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Eclipse Kepler Release updates (including Mylyn, EGit, m2e, m2e-wtp)</li>
<li>updated bundled tc Server to 2.9.2 and bundled Spring Roo to 1.2.4</li>
<li>ready for Spring 4</li>
<li>support for JavaConfig-driven Spring projects (including navigation support for @Autowired)</li>
<li>new and unified "New Spring Project" wizard</li>
<li>additional performance improvements for working with Spring projects</li>
<li>brand new instant and lightning fast quick search for your workspace</li>
<li>GGTS now includes grails 2.2.3</li>
</ul>
</div>
</section>
